# Temporary & Debug File Policy

## Rule: No temp files in project root

Never create debug scripts, temp files, or scratch files in the project root (`c:\jarvis\`).

## Designated directories

| File type | Location | Example |
|-----------|----------|---------|
| Debug / scratch scripts | `tmp/` | `tmp/_debug_sources.py` |
| Runtime logs | `logs/` | `logs/jarvis-start.log` |
| One-off data dumps | `tmp/` | `tmp/export_2026-04-19.json` |
| Test fixtures | `tests/fixtures/` | `tests/fixtures/sample.json` |

## Naming convention

- Prefix temp files with `_` (e.g. `_debug_`, `_temp_`, `_scratch_`)
- Include date if relevant: `_debug_scanner_2026-04-19.py`

## Cleanup

- `tmp/` contents are disposable — never commit them
- Add `tmp/` and `logs/` to `.gitignore` if not already present
- Delete temp files after the debugging session ends
